00:16:21,108 --> 00:16:24,900
- Your mom...
- Dad, I know she's different, okay? I see it too.

253
00:16:25,198 --> 00:16:27,191
Something happened to
her when you left.

254
00:16:27,236 --> 00:16:29,322
It got really bad.

255
00:16:29,748 --> 00:16:36,281
- Then, sometimes, she'd show up instead of Mom.
- She?

256
00:16:38,127 --> 00:16:39,412
Jessica.

257
00:16:40,336 --> 00:16:41,712
Jessica.

258
00:16:43,377 --> 00:16:46,003
Dad, Mom... Mom's sick.

259
00:16:46,508 --> 00:16:48,172
She can't help herself.

260
00:16:48,427 --> 00:16:50,213
She can't control it.

261
00:16:51,057 --> 00:16:52,263
Micah.

262
00:16:52,637 --> 00:16:55,342
Does your mom know
about Jessica?

263
00:16:56,476 --> 00:16:58,970
No, I don't think so.

264
00:17:01,487 --> 00:17:03,642
Dad, we can't just leave her.

265
00:17:06,777 --> 00:17:08,402
If you still love her,

266
00:17:08,657 --> 00:17:10,233
you'll help her.

267
00:17:13,656 --> 00:17:15,160
You're right.

268
00:17:24,047 --> 00:17:25,830
Do you know this boy?

269
00:17:26,177 --> 00:17:28,933
You're wasting my afternoon
because of a ridiculous dream.

270
00:17:28,966 --> 00:17:30,461
No  one said you had to come.

271
00:17:30,756 --> 00:17:32,600
And who's gonna keep
you from getting killed?

272
00:17:32,637 --> 00:17:34,023
This is a
dangerous neighborhood.

273
00:17:34,057 --> 00:17:36,691
One look at your fancy shoes and
we'll both be running for our lives.

274
00:17:36,725 --> 00:17:38,523
- Have you seen this boy?
- Come now, Mohinder.

275
00:17:38,558 --> 00:17:40,060
Let's stop this nonsense.

276
00:17:40,227 --> 00:17:43,891
Go back to the university,
talk about this like rational people.

277
00:17:43,898 --> 00:17:46,452
- I am not leaving until I find him.
- I know this boy.

278
00:17:46,487 --> 00:17:48,532
For 500 rupees,
I can tell you where he is.

279
00:17:48,566 --> 00:17:50,820
This man is a crook,
give him nothing.

280
00:17:51,077 --> 00:17:53,821
- What are you doing?
- Where?

281
00:18:17,637 --> 00:18:20,350
You came to me in my
dream last night.

282
00:18:20,645 --> 00:18:22,513
I don't come to anyone.

283
00:18:22,766 --> 00:18:26,061
- They come to me.
- Why?

284
00:18:26,318 --> 00:18:28,312
Why do they come to you?

285
00:18:28,355 --> 00:18:31,771
They have questions
that need answers.

286
00:18:32,238 --> 00:18:34,480
I'm not sure that
I have a question.

287
00:18:34,788 --> 00:18:37,952
Yes, you do.

288
00:18:43,125 --> 00:18:45,503
I have two paths
in front of me.

289
00:18:45,795 --> 00:18:47,503
I need to know
which one to take.

290
00:18:47,797 --> 00:18:50,791
Which one is my destiny.

291
00:18:51,677 --> 00:18:55,211
You already have
the answer you seek.

292
00:19:00,845 --> 00:19:02,263
What is it?

293
00:19:02,805 --> 00:19:04,893
What's my answer?

294
00:19:42,147 --> 00:19:43,183
Hiro.

295
00:19:47,066 --> 00:19:48,182
Excuse me.

296
00:19:49,148 --> 00:19:51,060
When was this picture taken?

297
00:19:51,277 --> 00:19:53,020
Oh, that was
Charlie's birthday.

298
00:19:53,238 --> 00:19:54,730
About six months ago.

299
00:19:56,287 --> 00:19:59,402
- Do you know him?
- Hiro? Sure.

300
00:19:59,578 --> 00:20:00,900
He and Charlie were tight.

301
00:20:01,205 --> 00:20:03,201
Please, where is he now?

302
00:20:03,417 --> 00:20:05,081
I have no idea, darlin'.

303
00:20:05,335 --> 00:20:07,661
He popped out of
her life weeks ago.

304
00:20:30,435 --> 00:20:33,602
Zach? What r u doing?

305
00:20:38,738 --> 00:20:41,653
Throwing rocks at ur window.
Open up!

306
00:20:54,927 --> 00:20:56,341
What's going on?

307
00:20:56,718 --> 00:20:58,552
I'm here to rescue you.

308
00:20:58,807 --> 00:21:00,551
- Let's go.
- I'm grounded.

309
00:21:00,927 --> 00:21:02,621
No one grounds the queen,
come on.

310
00:21:02,808 --> 00:21:04,300
Yeah, tell that to my dad.

311
00:21:04,687 --> 00:21:06,401
You only get to be
homecoming queen once.

312
00:21:06,436 --> 00:21:08,653
You know what?
You've already cemented your victory

313
00:21:08,686 --> 00:21:10,742
in the eyes of the student
body by punching Jackie.

314
00:21:10,775 --> 00:21:13,232
Plus, if you back out now,
she becomes the queen.

315
00:21:14,948 --> 00:21:16,902
My dad would pitch a fit.

316
00:21:17,525 --> 00:21:18,823
So, big deal. What?

317
00:21:19,155 --> 00:21:21,321
He grounds you more.
He double grounds you.

318
00:21:21,577 --> 00:21:23,901
Come on, you deserve this.

319
00:21:26,328 --> 00:21:28,413
I do deserve this.

320
00:21:28,708 --> 00:21:31,701
And tonight,
you can be my date to the dance.

321
00:21:34,335 --> 00:21:36,753
- Me?
- Sure, why not?

322
00:21:38,258 --> 00:21:40,420
Uh...

323
00:21:42,178 --> 00:21:44,802
For a million
different reasons.

324
00:21:45,225 --> 00:21:47,051
Is it about what Jackie said?

325
00:21:47,308 --> 00:21:50,362
- Because I don't care...
- I don't care about that, you think I care about that?

326
00:21:50,397 --> 00:21:53,493
She can call me whatever she wants.
I'm not gonna be embarrassed by it.

327
00:21:53,526 --> 00:21:54,482
I know who I am.

328
00:21:54,987 --> 00:21:56,600
I like who I am.

329
00:21:56,855 --> 00:21:58,611
I like who you are. I just...

330
00:21:59,116 --> 00:22:03,862
I  just wish that you
liked who you are.

331
00:22:04,158 --> 00:22:08,663
I'm finally realizing who
my friends really are.

332
00:22:09,125 --> 00:22:12,541
And that maybe being different
isn't the end of the world.

333
00:22:13,338 --> 00:22:15,210
That's just who I am.

334
00:22:15,505 --> 00:22:16,833
Exactly,

335
00:22:17,207 --> 00:22:19,463
you gotta embrace
your inner freak.

336
00:22:20,758 --> 00:22:23,510
Because the only thing
that you'll regret is

337
00:22:23,718 --> 00:22:25,840
denying who you really are.

338
00:22:35,897 --> 00:22:37,441
Ando?

339
00:22:40,236 --> 00:22:42,442
Hey, I'm Peter Petrelli.

340
00:22:42,697 --> 00:22:45,401
How are you?
So sorry it took forever.

341
00:22:45,656 --> 00:22:48,503
I-I couldn't get a flight,
and then taxis in this town...

342
00:22:48,617 --> 00:22:50,873
We still have time.
Where's... where's Hiro?

343
00:22:51,167 --> 00:22:53,583
Hiro traveled back in
time to rescue Charlie.

344
00:22:53,917 --> 00:22:55,560
I told him it
wasn't a good idea,

345
00:22:55,708 --> 00:22:57,850
Peter Petrelli might call,
but he insisted.

346
00:22:58,048 --> 00:23:00,540
- What happened to her?
- She was killed.

347
00:23:00,756 --> 00:23:05,672
We were sitting right here.
It happened so fast.

348
00:23:05,966 --> 00:23:09,272
Next thing we know, she was dead
and the killer was gone in a flash.

349
00:23:09,307 --> 00:23:14,310
Like, Okage. Uh... boogeyman.

350
00:23:14,645 --> 00:23:18,320
Hiro says maybe it is the same man that
is going to attack the cheerleader.

351
00:23:18,358 --> 00:23:20,901
I told Hiro do over,
is too risky.

352
00:23:21,105 --> 00:23:22,363
But Hiro says

353
00:23:22,657 --> 00:23:27,240
man who is too afraid to use power,
does not deserve to have power.

354
00:23:27,448 --> 00:23:28,572
I know when,

355
00:23:28,825 --> 00:23:32,173
and I know where the cheerleader
gets attacked. I have to stop him.

356
00:23:33,958 --> 00:23:36,872
- Is this you?
- Maybe.

357
00:23:37,876 --> 00:23:40,000
- You have a power, right?
- Sort of.

358
00:23:40,377 --> 00:23:43,630
Super strength?
You bend time and space like Hiro!

359
00:23:43,927 --> 00:23:48,341
No, I...I kind of absorb
the abilities of others.

360
00:23:48,597 --> 00:23:51,093
- But only when they're close.
- Hmm?

361
00:23:51,397 --> 00:23:54,470
Truthfully, when I'm by myself,
I don't...

362
00:23:54,685 --> 00:23:56,720
I'm not really anything.

363
00:24:01,525 --> 00:24:03,482
I've got less than an hour.

364
00:24:03,815 --> 00:24:06,151
Okay, it happens at 8:12,
I have to go.

365
00:24:06,828 --> 00:24:08,193
Coming?

366
00:24:09,535 --> 00:24:10,613
No.

367
00:24:10,956 --> 00:24:12,820
I will wait for Hiro.

368
00:24:13,127 --> 00:24:16,790
Without him,
I'm not really anything either.

369
00:24:17,625 --> 00:24:20,661
- Maybe you should wait too.
- There's no time.

370
00:24:20,916 --> 00:24:23,292
- I have to save the cheerleader.
- But, Peter!

371
00:24:26,386 --> 00:24:28,171
You die.

372
00:24:33,807 --> 00:24:37,263
- Where is she? She's gone!
- Oh, right.

373
00:24:37,685 --> 00:24:41,141
I saw her and Zach skip out
across the lawn ten minutes ago.

374
00:24:41,397 --> 00:24:43,351
She must have climbed
out her window.

375
00:24:43,778 --> 00:24:45,443
Why didn't you try to stop her?

376
00:24:45,735 --> 00:24:48,403
Because she's a good girl,
and she deserves this.

377
00:24:48,698 --> 00:24:50,651
You are being way too harsh.

378
00:24:53,865 --> 00:24:56,281
You don't know
what you've done.

379
00:24:57,288 --> 00:25:00,000
If you hear from her,
call me immediately!

380
00:25:07,138 --> 00:25:08,960
You're wasting your time.

381
00:25:09,216 --> 00:25:10,712
Freud would tell you the boy

382
00:25:11,137 --> 00:25:14,051
is merely a manifestation
of your subconscious.

383
00:25:14,348 --> 00:25:17,721
Nirad? Haven't we already
had this conversation?

384
00:25:27,028 --> 00:25:28,322
No, wait!

385
00:25:33,366 --> 00:25:34,912
You're wasting your time.

386
00:25:35,416 --> 00:25:39,411
Freud would tell you that the boy's
merely a manifestation of
your subconscious.

387
00:25:39,415 --> 00:25:41,220
It was more than a dream,
it was real.

388
00:25:41,256 --> 00:25:43,410
This boy can give me
the answers I seek.

389
00:25:43,718 --> 00:25:46,261
I'm your friend, Chandra,
but you sound like a madman.

390
00:25:46,298 --> 00:25:48,812
Well, all great thinkers were said
to be madmen in their time...

391
00:25:48,846 --> 00:25:50,462
Darwin, Einstein, Gandhi.

392
00:25:50,678 --> 00:25:53,730
Darwin was not ridiculed by his
university's biology round table.

393
00:25:53,767 --> 00:25:57,021
- They weren't even listening.
- You're the one who's not listening!

394
00:25:57,055 --> 00:25:59,553
You think you're actually
gonna find these people?

395
00:25:59,565 --> 00:26:01,890
Levitation,
spontaneous regeneration?

396
00:26:02,105 --> 00:26:05,943
Chandra, I know
that Shanti's death

397
00:26:06,196 --> 00:26:10,480
drove you to find answers,
but it is time to let go.

398
00:26:11,406 --> 00:26:14,533
If you persist on
espousing this

399
00:26:14,748 --> 00:26:17,612
insanity in your writing
and in your classroom,

400
00:26:17,785 --> 00:26:19,993
they will strip
you of your tenure.

401
00:26:27,718 --> 00:26:29,002
So be it.

402
00:26:49,907 --> 00:26:52,983
I just finished reading.
It's fantastic, Father.

403
00:26:53,238 --> 00:26:54,981
To think that today,
all around us,

404
00:26:55,077 --> 00:26:57,253
the evolutionary process
continues so dramatically!

405
00:26:57,285 --> 00:26:58,910
Who told you to read this?

406
00:26:59,168 --> 00:27:01,381
No one, I saw it on your desk,
so I picked it up.

407
00:27:01,415 --> 00:27:05,043
You invaded my privacy, Mohinder.
This was not for you to read.

408
00:27:05,255 --> 00:27:09,043
Well, I'm sorry, but I think it's
extraordinary, and I want to help.

409
00:27:09,336 --> 00:27:12,310
By using the Human Genome Project,
we can locate these people.

410
00:27:12,347 --> 00:27:14,762
Not "we"!
You can't be part of this.

411
00:27:15,057 --> 00:27:17,632
- Why not?
- Because I don't want you to be!

412
00:27:18,348 --> 00:27:20,640
I don't understand.

413
00:27:22,187 --> 00:27:25,973
Darwin said a scientific
man ought to have no wishes,

414
00:27:26,186 --> 00:27:28,272
no affections,
a heart of stone.

415
00:27:28,486 --> 00:27:31,232
That's me, Mohinder.
It's not you.

416
00:27:31,866 --> 00:27:33,652
Go home.

417
00:27:43,127 --> 00:27:45,201
You have your answer.

418
00:28:04,186 --> 00:28:06,272
You were trying to protect me.

419
00:28:41,388 --> 00:28:44,550
Heart of stone.
Why did you have a heart of stone?

420
00:28:44,898 --> 00:28:47,312
Heart of stone. Heart of stone.

421
00:28:53,855 --> 00:28:55,273
My sister.

422
00:29:10,087 --> 00:29:12,041
You found them.

423
00:29:32,777 --> 00:29:35,151
- Ooh, sorry!
- Sorry.

424
00:29:35,447 --> 00:29:38,141
That was my fault.
I wasn't looking where I was going.

425
00:29:38,445 --> 00:29:41,992
Hey, do you...
know this girl, Jackie Wilcox?

426
00:29:43,205 --> 00:29:46,872
Uh, yeah, half-time show
starts in about five minutes.

427
00:29:47,206 --> 00:29:50,042
She'll be out on the field.
She's a cheerleader.

428
00:29:52,335 --> 00:29:56,423
- Are you a reporter or something?
- Alumni.

429
00:29:56,637 --> 00:29:58,381
I'm just curious.

430
00:30:02,018 --> 00:30:06,642
You know, between you and me,
she's not that special.

431
00:30:06,976 --> 00:30:09,472
Just your average teenage girl.

432
00:30:09,725 --> 00:30:11,312
She rushed into a fire

433
00:30:11,606 --> 00:30:14,770
and saved a man's life,
sounds kinda special to me.

434
00:30:17,276 --> 00:30:19,311
Yeah, you're right.

435
00:30:19,735 --> 00:30:21,280
I'm jealous.

436
00:30:21,735 --> 00:30:24,703
She's our town hero. Me?

437
00:30:24,905 --> 00:30:27,743
I don't win too many
popularity contests.

438
00:30:28,205 --> 00:30:29,701
Hey, it gets better!

439
00:30:30,665 --> 00:30:34,620
- What?
- Life after high school.

440
00:30:34,965 --> 00:30:37,001
It gets a lot better.

441
00:31:34,607 --> 00:31:36,062
Half-time, girls!

442
00:31:36,315 --> 00:31:38,441
Come on, pump it up! Whoo!

443
00:31:45,945 --> 00:31:48,951
Will the nerviness never cease.

444
00:31:49,208 --> 00:31:51,032
I thought you were grounded.

445
00:31:51,785 --> 00:31:53,453
It didn't take.

446
00:31:54,795 --> 00:31:56,450
How's your eye?

447
00:31:56,836 --> 00:31:58,960
Nothing I can't cover up.

448
00:32:01,385 --> 00:32:03,232
There's something
I wanna say to you,

449
00:32:03,257 --> 00:32:05,250
cocaptain to cocaptain.

450
00:32:06,557 --> 00:32:08,091
Say it.

451
00:32:10,597 --> 00:32:13,013
I think you're a menace.

452
00:32:13,395 --> 00:32:15,561
And I'm not just
talking about you

453
00:32:15,895 --> 00:32:18,291
punching me over your boyfriend,
the girlfriend.

454
00:32:18,435 --> 00:32:20,140
I'm talking about
you in general.

455
00:32:20,448 --> 00:32:23,312
We used to be BFF's.

456
00:32:24,155 --> 00:32:25,733
What happened?

457
00:32:26,076 --> 00:32:28,530
Maybe I've gained
some perspective.

458
00:32:28,868 --> 00:32:31,362
I'm tired of trying to
be someone I'm not.

459
00:32:31,668 --> 00:32:33,842
Well, you've been trying to
be me since second grade.

460
00:32:33,875 --> 00:32:35,951
And now you're trying to be me.

461
00:32:36,208 --> 00:32:37,701
How do you figure?

462
00:32:38,086 --> 00:32:41,960
Your little heroic act of pulling the
guy out of the burning train car...

463
00:32:42,216 --> 00:32:44,461
wasn't your heroic act,
it was mine.

464
00:32:44,676 --> 00:32:46,170
No, it wasn't.

465
00:32:46,468 --> 00:32:48,170
I have it on tape.

466
00:32:54,648 --> 00:32:58,222
You know, a good friend of mine
once said it's more important to be

467
00:32:58,478 --> 00:33:01,692
honest with yourself
and happy than popular.

468
00:33:02,527 --> 00:33:04,941
I think he got it right.

469
00:33:06,656 --> 00:33:08,230
Really?

470
00:33:08,536 --> 00:33:10,780
Sounds like a loser to me.

471
00:33:13,457 --> 00:33:15,321
Public schools suck.

472
00:33:17,455 --> 00:33:19,621
- Did you hear that?
- Hear what?

473
00:33:30,635 --> 00:33:31,843
Hello?

474
00:33:31,845 --> 00:33:34,011
Stop it,
you're freaking me out!

475
00:33:34,268 --> 00:33:37,363
- I thought I heard something.
- You're imagining it. Let's go!

476
00:33:40,275 --> 00:33:43,850
- What is your problem?
- Don't go that way.

477
00:33:44,815 --> 00:33:46,311
What the hell?

478
00:33:46,617 --> 00:33:48,712
- Jackie, something's not right.
- No, duh!

479
00:33:48,826 --> 00:33:50,443
We're missing the coronation.

480
00:33:50,485 --> 00:33:52,833
Believe me, if you don't want to go out
there and get that homecoming crown,

481
00:33:52,865 --> 00:33:55,113
- I'm more than happy...
- Aah!

482
00:33:57,457 --> 00:34:00,331
No! No! No!

483
00:34:04,088 --> 00:34:05,621
Aah!

484
00:34:06,088 --> 00:34:07,423
Claire!

485
00:34:08,676 --> 00:34:11,670
Aah! Aah!

486
00:34:53,677 --> 00:34:55,260
Run.

487
00:35:05,526 --> 00:35:06,812
Are you okay?

488
00:35:09,406 --> 00:35:11,230
Run! Go!

489
00:35:13,077 --> 00:35:14,901
Keep going! Run!

490
00:35:29,045 --> 00:35:31,500
Oh, my God. Claire.

491
00:35:51,065 --> 00:35:53,731
Hey, hey, hey! Run!

492
00:35:57,196 --> 00:35:58,283
Run!

493
00:36:03,285 --> 00:36:05,741
- Who is it?
- Go, to the stadium, okay?

494
00:36:05,997 --> 00:36:08,381
Find people, find lights.
He doesn't want to be seen.

495
00:36:08,417 --> 00:36:09,722
- What about you?
- Don't worry about me.

496
00:36:09,757 --> 00:36:10,790
Just go!

497
00:36:11,125 --> 00:36:12,420
Go!

498
00:36:50,758 --> 00:36:51,673
No...

499
00:37:14,527 --> 00:37:15,653
You...

500
00:37:23,496 --> 00:37:24,820
How did you...

501
00:37:27,495 --> 00:37:28,831
Where is he?

502
00:37:29,545 --> 00:37:32,290
I don't know.
He ran away before I got here.

503
00:37:33,547 --> 00:37:36,130
Police. Go get some help, okay?

504
00:37:36,386 --> 00:37:37,920
Okay. I'll be back.

505
00:37:40,176 --> 00:37:41,840
Hey.

506
00:37:42,765 --> 00:37:44,222
What's your name?

507
00:37:44,846 --> 00:37:46,180
Peter.

508
00:37:47,477 --> 00:37:48,721
I'm Claire.

509
00:37:49,435 --> 00:37:50,930
Are you the one?

510
00:37:51,567 --> 00:37:54,523
By saving you,
did I save the world?

511
00:37:56,488 --> 00:37:57,810
I don't know.

512
00:37:59,575 --> 00:38:01,613
I'm just a cheerleader.

513
00:38:11,375 --> 00:38:12,753
Claire!

514
00:38:14,418 --> 00:38:17,001
Dad. Dad.

515
00:38:21,305 --> 00:38:24,303
It's okay. You're okay.

516
00:38:24,305 --> 00:38:26,182
Dad, it was terrible,
Jackie, she...

517
00:38:26,515 --> 00:38:28,143
I know, I know.

518
00:38:28,976 --> 00:38:30,602
We have to go back.

519
00:38:31,018 --> 00:38:32,683
We... we have to go back,

520
00:38:32,896 --> 00:38:34,101
- Peter...
- No, no, no.

521
00:38:34,356 --> 00:38:36,620
- He saved my life!
- No, no, no, he'll be fine.

522
00:38:36,658 --> 00:38:38,800
But we can't leave him.
We can't leave him.

523
00:38:38,986 --> 00:38:40,611
He almost died, but then he...

524
00:38:40,865 --> 00:38:43,493
He... We have to go back!
We have to go back!

525
00:38:43,825 --> 00:38:46,612
The police'll take
care of everything.

526
00:38:46,827 --> 00:38:48,281
Look at you.

527
00:38:49,665 --> 00:38:51,741
You're lucky to be alive.

528
00:38:51,997 --> 00:38:54,120
It's not luck, Dad.

529
00:38:56,336 --> 00:38:59,082
I have something I
have to tell you.

530
00:39:12,265 --> 00:39:14,143
You don't want to hurt me.

531
00:39:17,948 --> 00:39:20,151
We just need to talk.

532
00:39:22,576 --> 00:39:25,990
You can tell me
all about yourself.

533
00:39:26,536 --> 00:39:27,992
But first,

534
00:39:28,538 --> 00:39:29,820
go to sleep.

535
00:39:32,708 --> 00:39:34,792
You need to sleep.

536
00:39:54,018 --> 00:39:54,973
That's the guy!

537
00:39:54,976 --> 00:39:57,222
He's the one in the
overcoat the janitor saw.

538
00:39:57,277 --> 00:39:59,492
- Put your hands on your head!
- What the hell?

539
00:39:59,525 --> 00:40:02,163
- Look at all that blood.
- It's not what you think, guys!

540
00:40:02,198 --> 00:40:04,573
- All right, hands up.
- What are you do...

541
00:40:04,738 --> 00:40:05,780
It's not me!

542
00:40:06,038 --> 00:40:09,533
- He's getting away!
- Let's go! Stand up!

543
00:40:22,385 --> 00:40:23,961
Mira called.

544
00:40:24,297 --> 00:40:26,512
She said you turned
down her job offer.

545
00:40:27,518 --> 00:40:29,513
You're going back to New York?

546
00:40:31,898 --> 00:40:33,601
He did it, you know.

547
00:40:33,765 --> 00:40:34,763
He discovered them.

548
00:40:35,147 --> 00:40:36,642
His theory, it was right.

549
00:40:37,027 --> 00:40:39,062
And that is good news, yes?

550
00:40:39,696 --> 00:40:41,810
Why didn't he tell me?

551
00:40:42,355 --> 00:40:45,233
We wanted you to
live your own life.

552
00:40:45,778 --> 00:40:49,530
So now that you know about them,
what will you do?

553
00:40:49,746 --> 00:40:50,900
Find them.

554
00:40:51,328 --> 00:40:53,672
Tell them who they are,
if they don't already know.

555
00:40:53,705 --> 00:40:56,202
Warn them of the
dangers they face.

556
00:40:56,416 --> 00:40:58,370
And who will protect you?

557
00:41:10,638 --> 00:41:12,471
Next stop, Vegas.

558
00:41:12,765 --> 00:41:14,763
Dad, we don't need
to go back to Vegas.

559
00:41:15,225 --> 00:41:16,761
Why not?

560
00:41:17,317 --> 00:41:18,933
I called Mom.

561
00:41:19,476 --> 00:41:22,102
I told her where we are.
She's on her way.

562
00:41:23,106 --> 00:41:25,732
Micah, get in the car.
Now, come on!

563
00:41:27,028 --> 00:41:28,653
Dad, what's wrong?

564
00:41:28,987 --> 00:41:30,941
We are all, at our cores,

565
00:41:30,946 --> 00:41:32,911
the sum of our fears.

566
00:41:33,208 --> 00:41:36,122
To embrace destiny,
we must, inevitably,

567
00:41:36,165 --> 00:41:39,121
face those fears
and conquer them.

568
00:41:39,416 --> 00:41:41,412
Whether they come
from the familiar...

569
00:41:44,636 --> 00:41:46,712
or the unknown.

570
00:41:58,437 --> 00:42:00,720
My name is Hiro Nakamura!

571
00:42:02,236 --> 00:42:04,730
I'm here to save your life!

572
00:42:04,946 --> 00:42:06,443
Hey, Charlie!

573
00:42:06,778 --> 00:42:09,980
Charlie! Come over and
blow out the candles!

574
00:42:11,118 --> 00:42:14,360
Hold that thought, okay?
I gotta go make a wish.

